80.Remove the duplicates form sorted array II

Explanation 
it will check whether the count exceeds 2 and it will remove that element by left shift and make the count to 2 if it exceeds 3 and reduce the i-- to remain at the same position where each time the loop increases i++ so it is the reason to i-- after the rotation it should be remain at same position





int removeDuplicates(int* nums, int numsSize) {
    int i = 0;
    int c = 1;
    int n = numsSize;

    while (i < n - 1) {
        if (nums[i] == nums[i + 1]) {
            c++;
        } else {
            c = 1; 
        }

        if (c > 2) { 
            int j = i + 1;
            while (j < n - 1) {
                nums[j] = nums[j + 1];
                j++;
            }
            n--;      
            c--;   
            i--;   
        }
        i++;
    }

    return n;

}
